      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ELATED NZ (2) has returned in fine form having won both Victorian outings since a spell. Overcame a second line draw to get the prize by 1.7 metres at his latest appearance at Bendigo. A nice draw gives him the chance to land the hat trick. GEM N EM NZ (6) kicked off in Australia with back-to-back wins - one of them at this circuit and distance - before drawing on the back row and working to the front then fighting well to go under by a neck last start. Could atone with even luck. KUALIGHT (4) is a progressive mare who made it two wins from two runs this prep when she drew on the back line and raced three wide without cover before getting the cash by 6.5 metres at Shepparton. Really delivering now and could take this next step. KING SAINT (5) choked down and was pulled up last start but has claims off a second at Melton last month.",
